Rating: 1
The best I can say about this dish is that it's boring. If I had made it with leftover beef, instead of buying choice rib eyes for it, I probably wouldn't have been all that disappointed. It's missing something to give it some flavor. Between the rich ribeye and fatty cream, it's really sort of one-note. No acidic component. No zing. The onions and peppers aren't enough. Maybe top it with some horseradish creme fraiche? Maybe stir a little horseradish into the cream when it's added to the onion mixture. I don't know if I'm motivated to even try again with this one.

