Rating: 4
Made this with left over prime rib. Sauteed onions and broccoli with two strips of rendered bacon drippings, reduced with a little cream (what the heck?). Mixed in the meat & topped with Swiss cheese, broiled until melted then sprinkled crumbled bacon over the whole thing. OMGosh!! this was wonderful. You could really use this recipie and go anywhere with it depending on your leftovers. My husband loved this and called it pure comfort food. Very easy to do. Pop the potatos in the oven first thing through the door and a yummy meal is ready within an hour on a busy week night with only one pan to clean...my kind of weeknight meal!

